# artjr sketchbook -- Design System

Single source of truth for every visual, interaction, and content convention. Reference before writing or modifying any UI code. Tokens are defined in `src/index.css` (CSS custom properties) and wired through `tailwind.config.js`.

**Design philosophy:** Linear-inspired, dark-only, muted-rich, gallery aesthetic. The app frames sketches like art -- spacious, precise, and sophisticated.

---

## 1. Design Tokens

### Color Palette (dark-only)

All colors are CSS custom properties on `:root`. Never hardcode hex values in components.

**Two formats are used:**

- **RGB channels** (e.g. `9 9 11`) — for solid colors. These support Tailwind's `/opacity` modifier (e.g. `bg-accent/30`). Registered in Tailwind as `rgb(var(--x) / <alpha-value>)`.
- **Pre-baked rgba** (e.g. `rgba(124,58,237,0.15)`) — for colors with inherent transparency. These do NOT support `/opacity` modifiers. To get a dimmed variant, use the parent solid color with an explicit opacity value instead (e.g. use `bg-accent/[0.075]` instead of `bg-accent-soft/50`).

| Role | CSS Variable | Format | Tailwind | Supports /opacity? |
|------|-------------|--------|----------|--------------------|
| Base background | `--color-bg-base` | `9 9 11` | `bg-base` | Yes |
| Surface | `--color-bg-surface` | `19 19 22` | `bg-surface` | Yes |
| Elevated | `--color-bg-elevated` | `28 28 34` | `bg-elevated` | Yes |
| Hover | `--color-bg-hover` | `37 37 48` | `bg-hover` | Yes |
| Active | `--color-bg-active` | `46 46 58` | `bg-active` | Yes |
| Border | `--color-border` | `rgba(255,255,255,0.06)` | `border-border` | No |
| Border hover | `--color-border-hover` | `rgba(255,255,255,0.1)` | `border-border-hover` | No |
| Border focus | `--color-border-focus` | `124 58 237` | `border-accent` | Yes |
| Text primary | `--color-text` | `250 250 250` | `text-text` | Yes |
| Text secondary | `--color-text-secondary` | `161 161 170` | `text-secondary` | Yes |
| Text tertiary | `--color-text-tertiary` | `113 113 122` | `text-tertiary` | Yes |
| Accent | `--color-accent` | `124 58 237` | `text-accent` / `bg-accent` | Yes |
| Accent hover | `--color-accent-hover` | `109 40 217` | `bg-accent-hover` | Yes |
| Accent soft | `--color-accent-soft` | `rgba(124,58,237,0.15)` | `bg-accent-soft` | No |
| Accent muted | `--color-accent-muted` | `167 139 250` | `text-accent-muted` | Yes |
| Danger | `--color-danger` | `239 68 68` | `text-danger` | Yes |
| Danger soft | `--color-danger-soft` | `rgba(239,68,68,0.15)` | `bg-danger-soft` | No |
| Success | `--color-success` | `34 197 94` | `text-success` | Yes |
| Success soft | `--color-success-soft` | `rgba(34,197,94,0.15)` | `bg-success-soft` | No |

**Adding a new color:**
1. Add to `:root` in `src/index.css` — use RGB channels for solid colors, pre-baked rgba for transparent variants.
2. Register in `tailwind.config.js` under `theme.extend.colors` — use `rgb(var(--x) / <alpha-value>)` for RGB channels, `var(--x)` for pre-baked rgba.

### Tag Color Palette

10 auto-assigned muted colors for tag pills. Color is derived from a hash of the tag name.

`--tag-violet`, `--tag-blue`, `--tag-teal`, `--tag-emerald`, `--tag-amber`, `--tag-rose`, `--tag-pink`, `--tag-orange`, `--tag-cyan`, `--tag-lime`

Use the `<TagPill>` component (`src/components/ui/TagPill.tsx`) for all tag rendering.

### Border Radius

| Token | Value | Usage |
|-------|-------|-------|
| `rounded-sm` | 12px | Small containers |
| `rounded` (default) | 16px | Cards (`.card`), inputs |
| `rounded-lg` | 20px | Larger containers |
| `rounded-xl` | 24px | Modals, hero elements |
| `rounded-2xl` | 28px | Extra-large panels |
| `rounded-full` | 9999px | Buttons (`.btn`), icon buttons, pills, tag badges |

### Shadows

| Token | Usage |
|-------|-------|
| `shadow-card` | Default card elevation |
| `shadow-card-hover` | Card hover state (paired with translateY(-1px)) |
| `shadow-glow` | Accent-tinted glow for focused or highlighted elements |
| `shadow-modal` | Modals and overlays |

### Typography

**Font family:** Inter (Google Fonts) with system fallbacks. Registered as `font-sans` in Tailwind.

**Available weights:** 400 (Regular), 500 (Medium), 600 (Semibold), 700 (Bold).

**Headings use bold (700).** Body uses regular (400). Labels use medium (500).

Base body: `text-base leading-normal` (16px).

