## 5. Interaction and Motion

### Motion system (framer-motion)

All page-level and list animations use components from `src/components/ui/Motion.tsx`. Never write raw framer-motion `<motion.div>` inline when a primitive exists.

**Shared constants:**

| Constant | Value | Usage |
|----------|-------|-------|
| `EASE_OUT_EXPO` | `[0.16, 1, 0.3, 1]` | Primary easing -- smooth deceleration for enters |
| `EASE_OUT` | `[0.25, 0.46, 0.45, 0.94]` | Secondary easing -- fade-ins |
| `BASE_DURATION` | `0.45s` | Default animation duration |
| `STAGGER_INTERVAL` | `0.04s` | Delay between staggered children |

**Page sections -- staggered cascade:**

```tsx
<Stagger className="space-y-12">
  <StaggerItem>section 1</StaggerItem>
  <StaggerItem>section 2</StaggerItem>
  <StaggerItem>section 3</StaggerItem>
</Stagger>
```

Sections fade up (y: 10→0, opacity: 0→1) with 40ms stagger between each.

**Individual elements -- fade up:**

```tsx
<FadeUp delay={0.06}>content</FadeUp>
```

Use for toolbars, headers, standalone cards. Supports `delay`, `duration`, `distance` props.

**Table rows / list items -- staggered slide:**

```tsx
<StaggerList as="tbody" className="divide-y divide-border">
  <StaggerRow as="tr" className="...">row</StaggerRow>
</StaggerList>
```

Rows slide in from left (x: -8→0, opacity: 0→1) with 30ms stagger. Supports `as` prop for `div`, `tbody`, `ul`, `tr`, `li`.

**Grid cards -- staggered cascade:**

```tsx
<Stagger className="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-5">
  <StaggerItem><SketchCard .../></StaggerItem>
</Stagger>
```

**Modals -- scale + fade:**

Backdrop: `motion.div` with `opacity: 0→1`, 200ms.
Panel: `motion.div` with `scale: 0.95→1, y: 10→0, opacity: 0→1`, 250ms, `EASE_OUT_EXPO`, 40ms delay.

**Sidebar -- slide in from left:**

Sidebar container slides in (x: -20→0) over 400ms on mount. Nav items stagger in (x: -10→0) with 40ms intervals starting at 200ms delay.

**Page transitions:**

`<PageTransition>` uses `AnimatePresence mode="popLayout"` with route-keyed fade (opacity only, 180ms). No exit delay -- `popLayout` crossfades old/new simultaneously.

**Tab content:**

Wrap tab panels in `<FadeUp duration={0.3}>` for a quick reveal when switching tabs.

### Hover

- Cards: `hover:bg-hover transition-colors` or `.card-hover` (lift + shadow)
- Nav links: `hover:text-text` (from secondary)
- Buttons: defined in each `.btn-*` variant
- Links: no global hover underline. Use `.prose-link` class only on inline text links within notes, descriptions, and prose content

### Clickability

Every list item or table row that represents a navigable entity must be fully clickable. Apply the `.row-link` class to `<tr>` elements for consistent hover styling (background highlight on hover). Use `e.stopPropagation()` on any secondary interactive elements within the row (context menus, tags, action buttons) to prevent row navigation. Add `role="link"`, `tabIndex={0}`, and `onKeyDown` (Enter) for accessibility.

### Focus

All focusable inputs:

```
focus:border-accent focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-accent/30
```

(In `@apply` directives, use raw CSS: `.form-input:focus { --tw-ring-color: rgb(var(--color-accent) / 0.3); }`)

### Active / selected states

- Tabs: `border-b-2 -mb-px` with `border-accent text-accent` / `border-transparent text-secondary`
- View switcher: `bg-accent-soft text-accent` for active
- Sidebar nav: `bg-hover text-text` with accent icon

### Drag and drop

- Draggable: `cursor-grab active:cursor-grabbing`
- Dragging: `opacity-50`
- Drop target active: `border-accent bg-accent-soft`

### CSS transitions (non-motion)

- `transition-all duration-150` -- buttons, cards
- `transition-colors` -- rows, nav items
- `transition-opacity duration-200` -- transient UI

### Loading

- **Skeleton screens** for data fetches (use Skeleton components)
- **Top progress bar** (2px violet) on route changes
- Buttons while loading: `disabled:opacity-50`
- Inline loading spinner (rare): `<Loader2>` from lucide with `animate-spin`

### Disabled

```
disabled:opacity-50 disabled:cursor-not-allowed
```

