## 6. UX Patterns

### Empty states

Minimal centered prompt:

```html
<div class="py-10 text-center">
  <p class="m-0 text-sm text-secondary">No sketches yet</p>
</div>
```

Or inside a card: `<p class="p-10 m-0 text-secondary text-sm text-center">...</p>`

### Error states

- Inline: `<p class="text-sm text-danger m-0">...</p>`
- Page-level: `<p class="text-danger">...</p>`

### Navigation

Sidebar-based. Use `<Link>` from react-router-dom. Back links:

```html
<Link class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-sm text-secondary hover:text-text no-underline transition-colors">
  <ChevronLeft size={16} /> Back to sketches
</Link>
```

### Pagination

```html
<div class="flex items-center justify-center gap-3">
  <button class="btn"><ChevronLeft size={16} /> Previous</button>
  <span class="text-sm text-secondary tabular-nums">Page 1 of 5</span>
  <button class="btn">Next <ChevronRight size={16} /></button>
</div>
```

### Confirmation

Inline two-button pattern. "Are you sure?" with "Yes, delete" + "Cancel" side by side.

### Tag input

Inline input with dropdown suggestions. `<TagPill>` components left of input.

### Modals

Centered with backdrop. Drag handle: `<div class="w-10 h-1 rounded-full bg-border">`. Menu items are full-width rounded-xl buttons.

